  "target_response": {
    "text": "Keep going, with one adjustment: alternate hilly and flat routes for the next week or two rather than stacking hills every day. Sore calves after switching to climbs is a normal adaptation signal — hills shift load onto the calves and Achilles, and morning stiffness that eases once you're moving is the benign kind. Your data agrees this is adaptation rather than damage: today's recovery is 76% and your HRV is 64 ms, in line with your 63.2 ms baseline, so there's no systemic cost showing up. Two things that would change the advice: pain that turns sharp or one-sided, or Achilles pain that worsens as a run goes on instead of easing. Absent those, expect the soreness to fade as your calves catch up — usually within a couple of weeks of mixed routes.",
